<p>In this fairly simple setup, we=E2=80=99ll see ways of exploring how thi=
s system evolves over time.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"formal-definitions" class=3D"section level2">
<h2>Formal Definitions</h2>
<p>Some terminology here: We=E2=80=99re describing a <em>finite state</em> =
Markov chain. This means that there is a discrete (countable) set of possib=
le states to be in. For example, a child can be on the soccer field OR the =
playground and we ignore in-between states. We also say that the Markov cha=
in is <em>memoryless</em>, which means that the process is only dependent o=
n the <strong>current state</strong> of the chain. Each child=E2=80=99s pro=
bability of being, say, on the playground depends only on where they curren=
tly are. Let=E2=80=99s express these statements formally:</p>
