<p>So there=E2=80=99s a brief look at how Markov chains work. Markov chains=
 have vast applications, but where I come across them most often is their r=
ole in Bayesian computations. We didn=E2=80=99t go into this application he=
re, but hopefully after this you have an intuitive grasp of what a Markov c=
hain is.</p>
<p>Continue reading if you want to see how I coded the Markov chain and the=
 animations!</p>
</div>
