<div id=3D"behind-the-scenes" class=3D"section level1">
<h1>Behind the Scenes</h1>
<p>Below is the annotated code for creating and animating the Markov chain.=
 Feel free to customize it to your heart=E2=80=99s content.</p>
<div id=3D"building-the-simulation" class=3D"section level3">
<h3>Building the Simulation</h3>
<p>Here=E2=80=99s the function I created to run the Markov-based simulation=
. In our example, n is the number of children in the simulation. We specify=
 the number of iterations and provide starting probabilities for each of th=
e states and transition probabilities for the probability of moving from a =
state to another state. Note that in the binary case we don=E2=80=99t actua=
lly have to supply a matrix since we can leverage inverse probability.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"binary-state" class=3D"section level3">
<h3>Binary State</h3>
<pre class=3D"r"><code class=3D"hljs"><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">library<=
/span>(tidyverse) <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># includes ggplot2, dplyr, a=
nd others</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">library</span>(plotly)

markov1 &lt;- <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">function</span>(n =3D <span clas=
s=3D"hljs-number">100</span>, iter =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">100</spa=
n>, start_probs =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">.50</span>, <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">.50</span>), trans_probs =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number"=
>.10</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.05</span>), plot_prob =3D <span c=
lass=3D"hljs-literal">TRUE</span>) {
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#Check to see if probability entries are val=
id.</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(sum(start_probs) !=3D <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">1</span> | any(start_probs &lt; <span class=3D"hljs-number=
">0</span>))=20
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">stop</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"s=
tart_probs must be non-negative and sum to 1."</span>)
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(sum(trans_probs) &gt; <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">1</span> | any(trans_probs &lt; <span class=3D"hljs-number=
">0</span>))
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">stop</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"t=
rans_probs must be non-negative and not sum to greater than 1."</span>)

  dt &lt;- matrix(<span class=3D"hljs-literal">NA</span>, nrow =3D iter, nc=
ol =3D n) <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Initialize matrix to hold iteratio=
ns</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Run chain</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">for</span>(i <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">in=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:iter) {
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">for</span>(j <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">=
in</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:n) {
      <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(i =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-n=
umber">1</span>) { <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># if we're at the beginning=
 of the simulation</span>
        dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>,=
 <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number=
">1</span>, prob =3D start_probs)
      } <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span> {
        <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(dt[i - <span class=3D"hljs-n=
umber">1</span>, j] =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>) { <span cl=
ass=3D"hljs-comment"># if the previous state was 0</span>
          dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span=
>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-numb=
er">1</span>, prob =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span> - trans_probs=
[<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>], trans_probs[<span class=3D"hljs-num=
ber">1</span>]))
        } <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span> { <span class=3D"hljs-co=
mment"># if the previous state was not 0, we know it must have been 1</span=
>
          dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span=
>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-numb=
er">1</span>, prob =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span> - trans_probs=
[<span class=3D"hljs-number">2</span>], trans_probs[<span class=3D"hljs-num=
ber">2</span>]))
        }
      }
    }
  }
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Plot results?</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(plot_prob) {
    df &lt;- data.frame(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:iter, y =
=3D apply(dt, <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, mean))
    p &lt;- ggplot(df, aes(x, y)) +
      geom_line() +
      labs(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Iteration"</span>,
           y =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Prop."</span>) +
      theme_minimal(base_size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">16</span>)
   =20
    show(p)
  }
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Return chain as dataframe</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">return</span>(as.data.frame(dt))
}

df &lt;- markov1() <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># execute the function</spa=
n></code></pre>
</div>
<div id=3D"animating-the-binary-state-markov-chain" class=3D"section level3=
">
<h3>Animating the Binary State Markov Chain</h3>
<p>I used <a href=3D"https://plot.ly/r/">Plotly</a> to generate the animati=
ons. In the past I=E2=80=99ve tended toward gganimate because it integrates=
 really well with ggplot, but I find the result from Plotly to be sleeker.<=
/p>
<p>I=E2=80=99ve added a few aesthetic elements. First, some jittering to th=
e points to make them more visible. Second, I added some lag dependency (us=
ing dplyr=E2=80=99s <strong>lag</strong> function) and smoothing using the =
base <strong>spline</strong> function. This actually adds extra values to c=
reate the smooth transition, so we need to be careful with it.</p>
<p>The plotly code itself is fairly straightforward. A good resource for le=
arning plotly in R is through their <a href=3D"https://plot.ly/r/">website<=
/a>.</p>
<pre class=3D"r"><code class=3D"hljs">df_long &lt;- df %&gt;%
  rowid_to_column(var =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"iter"</span>) %&gt;%
  pivot_longer(cols =3D V1:V100) %&gt;%
  group_by(name) %&gt;%
  mutate(x_jitter =3D rnorm(n(), <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>, <spa=
n class=3D"hljs-number">.025</span>),
         x_jitter =3D x_jitter + lag(x_jitter, default =3D <span class=3D"h=
ljs-number">0</span>),
         x =3D value + x_jitter,
         y =3D rnorm(<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, <span class=3D"h=
ljs-number">0</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.01</span>),
         y =3D lag(y, default =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>) + r=
norm(n(), <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number"=
>.01</span>)) %&gt;%
  group_map(~ {
    value =3D .$value
    name =3D .y
    x =3D spline(.$iter, .$x)$y
    y =3D spline(.$iter, .$y)$y
    data.frame(name, value, x, y)
  })

df_full &lt;- do.call(rbind, df_long) %&gt;%
  group_by(name) %&gt;%
  mutate(initial =3D value[<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>],
         iter =3D row_number()) %&gt;%
  group_by(iter) %&gt;%
  mutate(prop1 =3D mean(value),
         prop0 =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span> - prop1)

anim1 &lt;- df_full %&gt;%
  plot_ly(
    x =3D ~x,
    y =3D ~y,
    color =3D ~factor(initial),
    size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">2</span>,
    colors =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"#FF7F00"</span>, <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"#1C86EE"</span>),
    frame =3D ~iter,
    type =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">'scatter'</span>,
    mode =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">'markers'</span>,
    showlegend =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
  )

anim1 &lt;- anim1 %&gt;%
  add_text(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, y =3D <span class=3D=
"hljs-number">.025</span>, text =3D ~prop1, textfont =3D list(color =3D <sp=
an class=3D"hljs-string">"#1C86EE"</span>, opacity =3D <span class=3D"hljs-=
number">.6</span>)) %&gt;%
  add_text(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>, y =3D <span class=3D=
"hljs-number">.025</span>, text =3D ~prop0, textfont =3D list(color =3D <sp=
an class=3D"hljs-string">"#FF7F00"</span>, opacity =3D <span class=3D"hljs-=
number">.6</span>))

ax &lt;- list(
  zeroline =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>,
  showline =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>,
  showticklabels =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>,
  showgrid =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>,
  title =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">""</span>
)

anim1 &lt;- anim1 %&gt;%
  layout(xaxis =3D ax, yaxis =3D ax) %&gt;%
  animation_opts(redraw =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>) %&gt=
;%
  animation_slider(hide =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">TRUE</span>) %&gt;=
%
  animation_button(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">.6</span>, y =3D <span=
 class=3D"hljs-number">.10</span>, showactive =3D <span class=3D"hljs-liter=
al">TRUE</span>, label =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Run Simulation"</sp=
an>) %&gt;%
  config(displayModeBar =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, scro=
llZoom =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, showTips =3D <span cl=
ass=3D"hljs-literal">FALSE</span>)
 =20
anim1</code></pre>
</div>
<div id=3D"building-the-triple-state-simulation" class=3D"section level3">
<h3>Building the Triple State Simulation</h3>
<p>The function for three states builds on the original binary state functi=
on. All that really needs to change is that the transition probabilities ar=
e captured in a matrix (although as we saw above, the binary state is techn=
ically a matrix too but we just don=E2=80=99t need to express it that way).=
</p>
<pre class=3D"r"><code class=3D"hljs">set.seed(<span class=3D"hljs-number">=
200322</span>)

markov2 &lt;- <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">function</span>(n =3D <span clas=
s=3D"hljs-number">100</span>, iter =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">100</spa=
n>, start_probs =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">.33</span>, <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">.33</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.34</span>), trans=
_probs =3D matrix(c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">.91</span>, <span class=3D"=
hljs-number">.11</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.16</span>,
                                                                           =
                     <span class=3D"hljs-number">.04</span>, <span class=3D=
"hljs-number">.79</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.10</span>,
                                                                           =
                     <span class=3D"hljs-number">.05</span>, <span class=3D=
"hljs-number">.10</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">.74</span>), ncol =3D=
 <span class=3D"hljs-number">3</span>),
                    plot_prob =3D <span class=3D"hljs-literal">TRUE</span>)=
 { <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Here we have a full non-zero transition m=
atrix.</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#Check to see if probability entries are val=
id.</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(sum(start_probs) !=3D <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">1</span> | any(start_probs &lt; <span class=3D"hljs-number=
">0</span>))=20
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">stop</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"s=
tart_probs must be non-negative and sum to 1."</span>)
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(any(apply(trans_probs, <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, sum) !=3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>))
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">stop</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"t=
rans_probs matrix rows must sum to 1."</span>)
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(any(trans_probs &lt; <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">0</span>))
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">stop</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"e=
lements of trans_probs must be non-negative"</span>)

  dt &lt;- matrix(<span class=3D"hljs-literal">NA</span>, nrow =3D iter, nc=
ol =3D n) <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Initialize matrix to hold iteratio=
ns</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Run chain</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">for</span>(i <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">in=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:iter) {
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">for</span>(j <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">=
in</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:n) {
      <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(i =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-n=
umber">1</span>) { <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># if we're at the beginning=
 of the simulation</span>
        dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>,=
 <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">2</span>=
), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, prob =3D start_probs)
      } <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span> {
        <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(dt[i - <span class=3D"hljs-n=
umber">1</span>, j] =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span>) { <span cl=
ass=3D"hljs-comment"># if the previous state was 0</span>
          dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span=
>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">2</spa=
n>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, prob =3D trans_probs[,<=
span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>])
        } <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span> <span class=3D"hljs-keyw=
ord">if</span> (dt[i - <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, j] =3D=3D <spa=
n class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>) { <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># if the p=
revious state was 1</span>
          dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span=
>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">2</spa=
n>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, prob =3D trans_probs[,<=
span class=3D"hljs-number">2</span>])
        } <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span> {
          dt[i, j] &lt;- sample(x =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-number">0</span=
>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-number">2</spa=
n>), size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, prob =3D trans_probs[,<=
span class=3D"hljs-number">3</span>])
        }
      }
    }
  }
 =20
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Plot results?</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span>(plot_prob) {
    df &lt;- data.frame(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>:iter,
                     n0 =3D apply(subset(dt =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-numb=
er">0</span>), <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, sum),
                     n1 =3D apply(subset(dt =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-numb=
er">1</span>), <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, sum),
                     n2 =3D apply(subset(dt =3D=3D <span class=3D"hljs-numb=
er">2</span>), <span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>, sum))
    p &lt;- df %&gt;%
      pivot_longer(cols =3D c(n0, n1, n2)) %&gt;%
      ggplot(aes(x, value, color =3D name)) +
      geom_line() +
      scale_color_discrete(labels =3D c(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"0"</sp=
an>, <span class=3D"hljs-string">"1"</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-string">"2=
"</span>)) +
      labs(x =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Iteration"</span>,
           y =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Prop."</span>) +
      theme_minimal(base_size =3D <span class=3D"hljs-number">16</span>)
   =20
    show(p)
  }
 =20
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Return chain as dataframe</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">return</span>(as.data.frame(dt))
}

df2 &lt;- markov2()</code></pre>
</div>
<div id=3D"animating-the-triple-state-markov-chain" class=3D"section level3=
